    <summary>A retro terminal file manager with synthwave aesthetics</summary>
    <description>
VHS-86 is a terminal-native file manager built in Rust, designed for users who love vim keys, neon colors, and the aesthetic of an 80s CRT monitor. Navigate your filesystem like it's 1986 — but with modern performance.

## Features

- **Vim-style navigation** — h j k l keys to move around
- **Dual-pane layout** — file list on the left, live preview on the right
- **Synthwave color scheme** — deep violet blacks, hot magenta, electric cyan, neon green, and gold highlights
- **File preview** — syntax-highlighted text files, directory contents, archive browsing
- **Advanced features** — batch operations, permission editor, disk usage analyzer, remote filesystem
- **Search & integration** — ripgrep-powered content search, shell commands, git status indicators
- **Plugin system** — WASM-based extensions for custom functionality
- **Customizable** — themes, keybindings, and configuration via TOML

## Requirements

- Windows 10 or later
- Windows Terminal or another modern terminal with truecolor support

## Usage

```
vhs-86 [OPTIONS] [PATH]
```

Run `vhs-86 --help` for full command-line options.
    </description>
